==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Retch
<hw>Retch</hw> <pr>(r⟦ecr⟧ch <it>or</it> r⟦emac⟧ch; 277)</pr>, <pos>v.
i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos> <conjf>Retched</conjf>
<pr>(r⟦ecr⟧cht)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Retching</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[AS. <ets>hr⟦ae⟧can</ets> to
clear the throat, hawk, fr. <ets>hraca</ets> throat; akin to G.
<ets>rachen</ets>, and perhaps to E. <ets>rack</ets> neck.]</ety>
<def>To make an effort to vomit; to strain, as in vomiting.</def>
<altsp>[Written also <asp>reach</asp>.]</altsp>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Beloved Julia, hear me still beseeching!⟦br⟧
(Here he grew inarticulate with <qex>retching</qex>.)</q>
<rj><qau>Byron.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retch</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Retch
<hw>Retch</hw>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Reck</er>.]</ety>
<def>To care for; to heed; to reck.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Retchless</ent>⟦br⟧
